@zploskey 
awesome, now do as in the example
`$rows = $this->db->get()->result_array();`

Thanks @zploskey 
Just for the record, I am using CI 3.1.5.
considering 'dbprefix' is 'ca_' !
Home controller 
```php
class Home extends CI_Controller {
	public function __construct()
	{
		parent::__construct();
		$this->load->database();
		$sql = $this->db
			->select(array('users.first_name', 'users.last_name'))
			->get_compiled_select('users', FALSE);
		echo $sql;  // output is perfect
		$rows = $this->db->get()->result_array(); // Error code 1054 [shown in attachment]
		die(var_export($rows));
	}
}
```
